IRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Bardfield was born in 1494, in Shenfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John Bardfield. She married George Gifford before February 1532, in Middle Claydon, Buckinghamshire, England. She died in 1539, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1494–1539":"1494–1539","1490–1530":"1490–1530","1495–1558":"1495–1558","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1558":"1558","before February 1532":"enne veebruari 1532","1555":"1555","1530":"1530","1495":"1495","1494":"1494","about 1530":"umbes 1530","1470":"1470","1539":"1539","1490":"1490","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shenfield, , Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Middle Claydon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Middle Claydon, Buckinghamshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"1494–1539":"1494–1539","1490–1530":"1490–1530","1495–1558":"1495–1558","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1470–Male":"1470–Kuollut","1558":"1558","before February 1532":"ennen vuotta helmikuu 1532","1555":"1555","1530":"1530","1495":"1495","1494":"1494","about 1530":"noin 1530","1470":"1470","1539":"1539","1490":"1490","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shenfield, , Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Middle Claydon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Middle Claydon, Buckinghamshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fr":{"1494–1539":"1494–1539","1490–1530":"1490–1530","1495–1558":"1495–1558","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1470–Male":"1470–Décédé","1558":"1558","before February 1532":"avant février 1532","1555":"1555","1530":"1530","1495":"1495